From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000002 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sound Tester <soundtester@invalid>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: bcm2835-i2s: only report a SYNC error when we own the
 clock

bcm2835_i2s_clear_fifos() clears the FIFOs and then confirms the clear by
toggling the CS_A SYNC bit and polling for it to change: the bit is meant
to flip after 2 PCM clock cycles.

That readback does not work when the BCM2835 is the clock slave -- the bit
is clocked by the external BCLK and never reflects the write -- which is
what the "FIXME: This does not seem to work for slave mode!" comment above
it has been saying all along. The poll therefore always runs to its
timeout and the driver prints "I2S SYNC error!".

The FIFO clear itself is unaffected. It needs 2 PCM clock cycles (0.33us
at 96kHz with a 64-bit frame) and the timeout loop spins on MMIO reads for
far longer than that, so the loop doubles as the required delay. Only the
verification is impossible in slave mode, so only report a failure when we
are the clock master and the result actually carries information.

On any card that makes the Pi a clock slave -- the Audio Injector Octo,
whose on-board FPGA drives BCLK and LRCLK, is the case at hand -- this
message otherwise appears on every stream setup: two lines on every boot,
with perfectly working 96kHz audio and zero xruns behind them. The cost is
not the noise. "I2S SYNC error!" is also the symptom of this card's real
and unfixed TDM slot-rotation bug, so crying wolf at every boot trains
whoever reads the log to ignore the one message that matters.

Signed-off-by: Sound Tester <soundtester@invalid>
---
 sound/soc/bcm/bcm2835-i2s.c | 46 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 40 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

--- a/sound/soc/bcm/bcm2835-i2s.c
+++ b/sound/soc/bcm/bcm2835-i2s.c
@@ -125,6 +125,19 @@
 	int					clk_rate;
 };
 
+/*
+ * True when the BCM2835 generates the bit clock. When an external device is the
+ * clock master (SND_SOC_DAIFMT_CBM_*), the PCM block is driven by that clock and
+ * a number of its status bits cannot be trusted -- see bcm2835_i2s_clear_fifos().
+ */
+static bool bcm2835_i2s_is_clock_master(struct bcm2835_i2s_dev *dev)
+{
+	unsigned int master = dev->fmt & SND_SOC_DAIFMT_MASTER_MASK;
+
+	return master == SND_SOC_DAIFMT_CBS_CFS ||
+	       master == SND_SOC_DAIFMT_CBS_CFM;
+}
+
 static void bcm2835_i2s_start_clock(struct bcm2835_i2s_dev *dev)
 {
 	unsigned int master = dev->fmt & SND_SOC_DAIFMT_MASTER_MASK;
@@ -188,8 +201,24 @@
 	/* Wait for 2 PCM clock cycles */
 
 	/*
-	 * Toggle the SYNC flag. After 2 PCM clock cycles it can be read back
-	 * FIXME: This does not seem to work for slave mode!
+	 * Toggle the SYNC flag. After 2 PCM clock cycles it can be read back.
+	 *
+	 * This readback does not work when we are the clock slave: the flag is
+	 * clocked by the external BCLK and never reflects the write, so the
+	 * poll below always runs to its timeout. That is what the long-standing
+	 * "FIXME: This does not seem to work for slave mode!" here referred to.
+	 *
+	 * The FIFO clear itself is fine either way -- it needs 2 PCM clocks
+	 * (0.33us at 96kHz x 64), and the timeout loop spends far longer than
+	 * that spinning on MMIO reads, so it doubles as the required delay.
+	 * Only the *verification* is impossible, so only report a failure when
+	 * we are the clock master and the answer therefore means something.
+	 *
+	 * Cards that make the Pi a clock slave (e.g. the Audio Injector Octo,
+	 * whose FPGA drives BCLK/LRCLK) otherwise print "I2S SYNC error!" on
+	 * every single stream setup. That trains the operator to ignore this
+	 * message -- which is exactly the message that reports the card's real
+	 * TDM slot-rotation fault when it happens at runtime.
 	 */
 	regmap_read(dev->i2s_regmap, BCM2835_I2S_CS_A_REG, &syncval);
 	syncval &= BCM2835_I2S_SYNC;
@@ -204,8 +233,13 @@
 			break;
 	}
 
-	if (!timeout)
-		dev_err(dev->dev, "I2S SYNC error!\n");
+	if (!timeout) {
+		if (bcm2835_i2s_is_clock_master(dev))
+			dev_err(dev->dev, "I2S SYNC error!\n");
+		else
+			dev_dbg(dev->dev,
+				"I2S SYNC flag not readable in slave mode (expected)\n");
+	}
 
 	/* Stop clock if it was not running before */
 	if (!clk_was_prepared)

--
2.34.1
